    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Augers made in the form of a tapered, conical half-funnel, with one or both of the exposed edges side-sharpened to cut laterally. They are used to cut conical holes for coopers, ladder makers, wheelwrights, chair makers, and for other purposes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000036401/Salaman, Dictionary of Tools Used in Woodworking (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000077354/Underhill and Underhill, Woodwright's Guide (2009)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Boren die zijn gevormd als een taps toelopende, conische halve trechter waarvan één of beide open zijkanten zijn gescherpt om zijdelings te snijden</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
